<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes_for_Week_4:_5.1_Introduction_to_Per-Unit_Taxes">Notes for Week 4: 5.1 Introduction to Per-Unit Taxes</span></h2>
<p>THREE MAIN INPUTS</p>
<ol>
<li><p>Gas in Chicago: very expensive because of many taxes adding up</p></li>
<li><p>Who share most of the burden of the tax (consumer or producer)?</p></li>
</ol>
<p>•   Example: girlfriend and boyfriend moving apart; she is more into the relationship than him (her demand is more inelastic); she will be doing all the flights </p>
<p>•   The side of the market which is more inelastic (having more trouble to adjust to the change) will be the one paying the burden</p>
<ol>
<li>What is the burden of the tax on the market?</li>
</ol>

